x4freetext: Experiments were performed at the
Indiana University Cyclotron Facility
Helium gas target cell operated at a pressure of 267
Torr
A four element
detector telescope was employed for mass, charge, and
energy identification of light ions. The telescope
consisted of three surface-barrier silicon detectors
of thicknesses 50 pm, 1 mm, and 2 mm, followed by a 5
mm Si(Li) detector, tilted at 60 deg in order to stop
elastically-scattered He ions.
